<h1>Welcome to the DevJobs</h1>
<%#= render 'visitors/carousel' %>
<p><%= link_to 'Users:', users_path %> <%= User.count %> registered</p>
<div class="row">









  <div class="col-sm-4">
    <h3>Cup of Morning Coffee </h3>


   <p> This is a website will contain international development­related news and content and serves as a one­stop shop
    for posting and searching for related jobs.</p>

    <p>The website will emphasis donor markets with the most money. Off the top of my head:

    USAID, DFID and Australia. EU Commission funds a lot of work. Why do they not appear on

    Devex more? Is there another site the Europeans are using?</p>






      <h3>Search by Technical Area</h3>
      <ul>
      <% @alltechnicalareas.each do |tech| %>
         <li><%= link_to tech.name, tech %></li>
      <% end %>
      </ul>


    <h3>Search by Category</h3>
    <ul>
      <% @allcategories.each do |cat| %>
          <li><%= link_to cat.name, cat %></li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>


















  </div>












  <div class="col-sm-4">
    <h3>Latest Opportunities</h3>
    <% @latestnotices.each do |ad| %>
       <strong><%= link_to ad.name, ad %></strong><br>
       <%= ad.organization.name %><br>
        <%= ad.level.name if ad.level_id.present? %><br>
        <%= ad.jobtype.name if ad.jobtype_id.present?  %><br>
<hr>

    <% end %>



  </div>



  <div class="col-sm-4">
    <h3>In The Field...</h3>
    <% @latestposts.each do |post| %>
        <strong><%= link_to post.name, post %></strong><br>
        <%= post.created_at %><br>

        <hr>

    <% end %>



  </div>



</div>